cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the trade-offs between centralized and distributed control planes in cloud frameworks and proposes a new abstraction for scheduling tasks in a distributed system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a new control plane abstraction for data analytics frameworks. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper discusses the scheduling of tasks in a data analytics framework. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new abstraction for scheduling tasks in a software system. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of program control flow to cache frequently-executed tasks.
